Modify the structure of tables.
Alter command is used to change the structure of the table.

Drop,add or repositioning a column
alter table practice drop column_name;
alter table practice ADD column_name int;
alter table practice ADD column_name i after column2;

Modify:
alter table practice modify column_name char(10);

table name change:
alter table practice to practice2;

alter table practice rename column id to roll;
alter table practice add primary key(roll_no);

drop table practice;

Add constraint using alter table:
1) Add Primary Key-> alter table tablename ADD Primary Key(column_name);
2) Add Foreign Key-> alter table tablename Add Constraint CK Foreign Key(column_name) References tablename;

We can drop the integrity constraint later on if we can not need that.
alter table tablename drop Primary Key.
alter table tablename drop Constraint constraintname; // like CK


